{"id": "1527687444093468722", "channel_id": "1527269079784886362", "author_id": "304652156286533642", "author_name": "sbpan", "content": "There are several ways to play this, I can only offer my own style.\n\nFirst, you use Thaïs to feed lots of aliemus to Saya. Don't forget to use Saya's 2 to collect gynoceum when you can afford it.\nAs soon as you can, rouse Saya to give her even more aliemus from rewritten card.\nThen rouse Thaïs to unlock the double devour.\n\nFirst part of the fight : use Saya's exalt to copy Thaïs until all awakeners are close to exalt\n\nSecond part of the fight : flood your deck with copies of Corpo\n\n3 points to keep in mind :\n- Copies from Thaïs or Saya are destroyed at turn end *if they remain in your hand* meaning it's safe to discard a 0-cost Ancient caress for example.\n- Corpo's 4-cost can be brought down to free if you discard it enough. This means you can copy Lightning retribution with Thaïs > 3-cost then shuffle with Saya > 2-cost then shuffle with Aurita > 1-cost then shuffle with Corpo > 0-cost.\n- There are variations to this linup but one part stays true : always keep Saya's viscera blossom in hand ( you can discard it but it won't auto-discard at turn end ) until you're ready to strike hard", "timestamp": "2026-07-17T14:44:29.732000+00:00", "thread_id": "1527269079784886362", "edited_timestamp": "2026-07-17T14:44:48.021000+00:00"}
{"id": "1527687641443864697", "channel_id": "1527269079784886362", "author_id": "304652156286533642", "author_name": "sbpan", "content": "Still, I feel I must emphasize that this linup is not one I would recommand for new players.\nBut it's fun ^^", "timestamp": "2026-07-17T14:45:16.784000+00:00", "thread_id": "1527269079784886362"}
